title: What to include in your course
New Block Title
body:
If you need to add a video it can be done in two ways. 

1. If your video is on youtube you can add in the 'youtube player' component seen on the right here. It will allow you to just embed the video directly from youtube and bring across captions. However you need to be aware you cannot add in a transcript on this option, and the captions are often auto generated by youtube and can be wrong so you will need to check this. If you own the video channel you can make the changes to the captions yourself directly on youtube (https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/2734705?hl=en-GB). If you do not own the video you will need to use option two. 

 

 

 

2. Add your video as either an MP4 or youtube link, and add in captions (CC) and transcript yourself by using the media component seen on the left here. This is a little more fiddly but ensures the captions are accurate. You need to create something called a VTT file (detailed instructions), and it's easiest to create/edit in notepad (I will add in a link for a blank file once sharepoint has migrated).  There is a useful VTT checker online which will allow you to see if there are any formatting mistakes in your file such as additional spaces or full stops. You should then save the format in notepad as ending with en.vtt . and from the drop down select "All files" rather than text. Once it's saved in a VTT format you can upload it to adapt within the relevant box.

title: Did you know...
body: that you can add resources to your course. Check out the menu in the top right of this screen, you should be able to see accessibility and captions files.

title: Example accordion component
body:
An accordion is set of clickable sections, they are completely keyboard navigable.

You don't need an image for each of the sections, the ones used in this accordion are placeholders only, you can delete them out and use your own if you wish. 

There is no set amount of sections you have within an accordion but as a guide six a good maximum and three as a minimum


Please leave the instruction text in (or modify if needed) as this will give the instruction to screen readers.

title: HTML code
body: There might be some occasions where you need to add in some HTML functions to your course e.g. additional buttons, amending the font size and so on. These are some examples of the code you will need to enter and how to customise and edit it.

title: Example narrative
body:
A narrative is a carousel type interactive where users can click though an image and text within the same block. 

Images are required for this one, placeholder images have been used in this example.
